items.text: Sushi is okay but pieces are very small
Great view. Drinks are priced to reflect the great view. Come here for a treat.
Great view!!!!!!
The Chirashi bowl is excellent. Very fresh. Black sesame ice cream is very memorable.
Good after work place for drinks. The place gets more chaotic as people get drunk. Nice view and casual dress code- not pretentious like other rooftop bars.
This is likely one of the most overrated places in Singapore; mostly by expats. It's expensive and every piece of sushi has frozen crab meat filler.
Good view but the quality of food is not worth the price paid. Will not go a second time.
The spider maki and the garlic fried rice were both great!
Great service early on. Nice Japanese style.
Rooftop place with an amazing view of MBS.
Love the rooftop bar. Try the Chili wasabi (Japanese sounding) martini 👍
Ask for the off-menu maguro salad. Tuna for y'all gaijin :)
Nice shld try
Ok quality and freshness..limited selection of sushi..great ambience
The nori breadcrumb spicy salmon is my all-favourite set lunch on the menu. Great for business lunches with a fantastic picturesque view of the MBS!
I can't believe they only have restrooms at level 1 and not at the rooftop bar
The Kinki fish is in! And the new seasonal Japanese fruits are absolutely yummy! Shizuoka melon and sakurambo cherries anyone?
Best bar with a view, but I recommend booking a table, even in the early part of the night.
Great place! Great crowd 😎
Obnoxious bar staff
Decorated with feisty urban murals to reflect its philosophy and pop-culture credo, this 60-seater also prides itself on having fresh, well-sourced ingredients for innovative dishes.
Order the geisha cocktail. Lovely views with really chilled music.
Service is nothing to shout about considering the price of this place. Lunch sets are so-so. Great view tho if you can get a window seat.
Generally pricey dishes, but for something friendlier on your wallet, there's the $8++ snow crab sashimi. Also try the wasabi cocktail. Review at http://sparklette.net/food/kinki-restaurant-bar/
Fancy. No joke.
Great place for pre/post dinner drinks. Easy chic, great throwback music. And great view of the Marina :)
Food is oj but the bar has a great view and fantastic happy hour!
Great place, get a table at roof top bar alongside river!
Great rooftop bar with a view!
Great ambience
Great Japanese food. Pricey but worth it!
Happy Hour at the Rooftop bar starts at 5pm.. 1 for 1 housepour wines,spirits and beers. Don't miss out on that!
Simply outstanding sushi. Sashimi amazing. Foie Gras very original.
Nice atmosphere if you don't go on a Friday night (too packed), the kinki nachos are delicious.
Amazing view with great worth of price for drinks
Foie Gras Sushi - YUM!!Oh and cod and pomegranate is just amazing...
Seating: Ask 4 seats by d windows 4 a gr8 view of d bay - day or nite!
Chirashi $40++,Not worth the money. Mazachirashi @ Aoki $40++ with much higher quality fish.
HAPPY HOUR :one for one from 5pm - 8pm
Excellent modern Japanese. California roll with REAL crab meat instead of crabstick. Tempura prawn and spicy tuna maki is yum. Funky interior and roof bar
Ask for a table by the window. The tai carpaccio with truffle oil is worth it, as is going upstairs to the rooftop bar after dinner.
A nice view of the bay upstairs, but it can be a bit loud with Top 40 pop music. Advised not to go when it's raining as the undercover is not quite sheltered from the rain. Service is friendly.
Hip hop Friday. www.findyourwayinsg.sg
Nice n relax place
Super cool Japanese restaurant. After dinner go to the terrace and enjoy the views of the marina bay
Cod, dragon rolls, spicy edamame
The yuzu umeshu tastes like orange juice with vodka. Definitely the cocktails are not good.
Worst service ever. You should buy as many drinks as you can at once.
Very good place for after work drinks and japanese fusion cuisine afterwards
Nice place to hang out especially at night!
Great view! Must try the Wagyu foie gras donburi.
Do yourself a favour and order the king salmon maki. Dreams are made of this. Impressed with service here.
Great spot for drinks after work. Happy hours (1for1) till 9pm. Food is a bit pricey.
We spent new years eve here. Great location, and excellent place to see the fireworks and perfect to get hammered 😂
Chef Kinki opens for lunch from 31 May! Oishiiness starts from 12pm. Yum!
The Fois Gras Scallop sushi is to die for! One is not enough.
Music is 90's.
View and food
The Foie Gras & Hokkaido Scallop is absolutely oishii. Check out other Kinki's customs on the menu for dishes that were specially created for and only available at Kinki.
Try the pear martini on the secret roof top! Good music  and stellar view!
Sashimi and sushi are good. But not the cooked items and fried maki. Oil in food gave me stomach pain.
The window seat view is awesome. Also try the kurobuta katsu curry!
Fresh salmon sashimi, foie gras & scallop sushi is extremely good, nice unagi fried rice (Japanese sticky rice), the crispy pork belly is just okay.
Great miso, very fresh edamame with sea salt flakes, mango salmon maki,  spicy tuna maki, great green tea icecream...Really good atmosphere... :)
Fantastic sashimi and the spicy salmon (even for a non-spicy lover like me as it doesnt have chili). Also try the gin berry at the rooftop bar
So crowded and so expensive
Everyone is smoking at the rooftop terrace. There in no Japanese beer on tap. Cocktails are boring. Avoid! For a good view and drinks go to Loof, Lantern or Smoke & Mirrors.
Always fab place.
Really enjoyed the food but service was horridly unorganized although friendly. Cool space, tasty fish!
